syncronizer dying, ?

> Why does this help?

it's called "double clutching" and it is the standard way of shifting on
gearboxes that are not syncronized or by many to put less load on the
tranny

> What else can I do?

get good at double clutching and look for a good tranny?

might be adjustment but you said you played with that

take all of what I said with care I have only had automatics in the past
ten years and knowledge is rusty on manuals

